rComments: Bunner complemented Gombay's lectures very well. While Gombay simplified these complex ideas and explained them to us in a conversational tone (which was great), Bunner supplemented us with the details. He drew charts, made important definitions and distinctions clear, and he did this in a very accessible way. Very helpful.
Answers too many questions but was definitely clear, nice and knowledgeable.

Welcome to Amateur Hour. A T.A. who taught PHL210Y (17th and 18h Cent. Phil) in the summer 2011 session and it had to be his first course (or at least better have been!). He is painfully insecure, lacks confidence, and takes/encourages way too many questions which he is inept at answering. He just says "cool, yeah good". No instruction at all.
